stuart coulson our point of view innovators not innovations our way of working real world projects radical collaboration learning experiences take a d school class use our methods attend executive education be a project partner get a degree browse our reading list the latest d news blog social entrepreneurship k 12 education press about us our team tours faqs getting to our building contact us d school d school d school institute of design at stanford our team we couldn t be more different except for our shared values and that makes working together enjoyable stuart coulson lecturer entrepreneurial design for extreme affordability stuart discovered entrepreneurial design for extreme affordability at the d school and knew he had found the perfect place to use his experience and interests to try to do some good while at the same time continuing to learn and grow his skills after mounting a significant pester campaign the extreme teaching team finally gave in and offered stuart a chance to join them since then stuart has become steadily more involved with the course and has so far managed to hide the fact that he is learning far more than he is teaching stuart tries to bring his entrepreneurial and commercial background to the process of business planning with the extreme project teams and is interested in how design thinking is best applied to that aspect of the innovation process stuart was born and raised in ireland but has lived and worked in various parts of the world before moving to palo alto it would be nice to list a bunch of diverse extra curricular interests but apart from enjoying playing with his kids sadly or luckily stuart's hobbies are business entrepreneurship innovation economics and venture funding he buys far more non fiction books than he will ever be able to read and lives vicariously through the excitement enthusiasm and vitality of the startup teams he works with who's here in 2011 2012 adam royalty adam royalty alex kazaks alex kazaks banny ban